                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-111-victim1231 t18211205-111-viclabel687"></join>. On the 20th of November, I was driving a load of mahogany from the West India Docks; I stopped the waggon at a gate, in <placeName id="t18211205-111-crimeloc688">Rosemary-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-111-crimeloc688" type="placeName" value="Rosemary-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18211205-111-crimeloc688" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18211205-111-off685 t18211205-111-crimeloc688"></join>, about half-past six o'clock, and while I was gone for the key, two cloths and a sack were taken from the box - I went in pursuit, and found the prisoner standing in the lane about three hundred yards off, he had nothing - I fetched Hamilton, who said he was the man, and I took him; I have not found the things.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18211205-111-person1234">
                  JANE 
                  HAMILTON
